# 'ejabberd' module -- Configure and manage ejabberd

This directory holds the definition of the Puppet module 'ejabberd' 

## Description

Configure and manage ejabberd
## Directory organization 

    modules/
      `-- ejabberd/       # Main directory for the 'ejabberd' module
           `-- Modulefile        # Module configuration - cf [here](https://github.com/puppetlabs/puppet-module-tool)
           `-- README            # This file
           `-- files/            # Module files
           `-- lib/              # custom facts/type/provider definitions
           `-- manifests/
                `-- init.pp      # Main manifests file
                `-- classes/     # Hold manifest for ejabberd classes/
                     `-- ejabberd.pp         # defines the ejabberd class
                     `-- ejabberd-params.pp  # ejabberd module variables 
                `-- definitions/ # Hold manifest for ejabberd definitions
                     `-- ejabberd-mydef.pp   # defines the ejabberd::mydef definition               

           `-- templates/        # Module ERB template files
           `-- tests/            # Module testing files (NOT YET IPLEMENTED)


## Documentation

Please refer to the header of each manifest files to understand the usage of classes and definitions associated to the 'ejabberd' module.
 
Alternatively, generate automatically the documentation via [`puppet doc`](http://docs.puppetlabs.com/man/doc.html) as follows: 

       $> rake doc
       
For other information, please refer to:

* the `Moduleinfo` file in this directory 
* the `README` file of the `puppet-repo` repository. 

